Kemp, J. "Time to be afraid - preparing for the next big solar storm". Reuters. July 2014.

NOTES: In 1859, the Carrington event measured at 850. In March 1989, there was a 589 that caused a major blackout in Quebec and other problems. A July 2012 storm was measured at 1,200 that narrowly missed Earth
